b'@mansiimunjal and we at Tata Motors, salute @munjalneeru for her immense dedication on doing her bit to make #HumanityAboveAll.

Here\xe2\x80\x99s her story: 
Neeru Munjal, resident of Colaba, has been feeding over 12 dogs since the past 5 years without fail, no matter what. 
With restrictions on movement during Covid-19 crisis, undeterred, every evening at 5pm she ensures that all her dogs receive their staple meal of rice and chicken cooked lovingly at home. 
Seen in the picture are two of these dogs being fed away from residential areas to ensure cleanliness as well as adherence to all rules of dog feeding during lockdown.'

b'We at Tata Motors, salute @sanjshrd_ for her immense dedication on doing her bit to make #HumanityAboveAll. \nHere\xe2\x80\x99s her story: \nSanjana Sharda is a dog lover at heart! During these trying times, she ensures that every evening she feeds 9-10 stray dogs in Goregaon East! We salute her and love her enthusiasm to put #HumanityAboveAll.'

b"We at Tata Motors, salute @nikitadcruz19 for her immense dedication in doing her bit to make #HumanityAboveAll. 
Here is her story: 
Nikita D'cruz along with her team at India Fellow are making cash available in the bank accounts of migrant workers and daily wage earners across urban and rural India. Over the last 40 days, more than INR 50 lakh has been made available for 5000+ people including construction labourers; migrant workers, sex workers, religious violence victims and farmers amongst others.
They all need cash not just for groceries, medicines, mobile recharge but also to have a choice in what they eat, to feel dignified and relieved.
With the changing nature of distress, the team continues to provide cash relief. They're additionally focusing on a regular support for families with INR 2000 per month for the next 3 months."
